sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lisa Oberding, Ali Honarmand
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: DszB amplified from an environmental isolate of Rhodococcus that is an active desulfurizer, promotor from registry.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DszC with B0034. Built in collaboration with the University of British Colombia iGEM Team.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dszB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: HBPS desulfinase (DszB) from R. erythropolis (mutated for improved activity)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DszB - HBPS desulfinase which carries out the last step of the 4S pathway, converting 2-hydroxybiphenyl-2-sulfinic acid (HBPS) to 2-hydroxybiphenyl. The sequence has been mutated Y63F to increase enzyme activity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lisa Oberding, Ali Honarmand
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Amplified from a plasmid in an environmental isolate of Rhodococcus shown to be an active desulfurizer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Mutations of internal PstI and NotI cut sites in order to make biobrick compatible, as well as an added mutation of Y63F in the protein to increase its activity.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K804005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a DszC coding gene from the DszABC operon in the 4S pathway of Rhodococcus erythropolis IGTS8. It encodes one of the three biodesulfurizing enzymes in the DszABC operon. DszC enzymes have been shown to catalyze dibenzothiophene (DBT)to dibenzothiophene-5-oxide (DBTO) in the first reaction and then from DBTO to DBT sulfoxide (DBTO2) in the second reaction, both in the presence of NADH, FMN and flavin reductases.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Joe Ho
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: 2 PstI sites were removed using site-directed mutagenesis
